Dear Sir,
I have dispatched this messenger with regard to my two young dogs.
It has pleased you to grant them to me.
I have been requested to meet Mr. High Sheriff
tomorrow in Newcastle regarding the bene
volence. I kindly request that you provide me with a
brief updateon the situation in the area and
the actions taken, considering
that we are all united in our
cause. With the remembrance of my affection
for you and my good cousin, your bedfellow,
I remain
Your relative and steadfast
frend,
Thomas Crompton
Stone, 12th 
June 1622


To the esteemed and
dear cousin,
Walter Bagott, Esquire,
at Blythfield. Please deliver this message.
